        /// <para>The spatio-temporal clustering feature classifies files in a dataset based on their time and location. This feature works on indexed files, such as images and videos, that contain shooting time and location data. These classifications can represent content from a user\&quot;s trip, where files have similar timestamps and locations. The classifications can also represent content shot at different places where a user lives or works. Analyzing the locations and time ranges of these classifications lets you categorize media files, create highlight reels, and generate photo and video stories.</para>
